"{\"uid\": \"theinertia.com-surf-revised-teahupoo-olympic-judging-tower-backed-by-french-polynesian-president\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Photo: 2019 Tahiti Pro//WSL  The judging tower at the future Olympic surfing venue of Teahupo'o has been a subject of controversy for some time now.Earlier this year, concerns over damage to the reef prompted protesters to demand that construction of the new tower be scrapped.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.7419946139441399, \"rank\": 0.3477186777466719, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their proposed solution was to reuse a wooden tower the WSL has used in earlier broadcasts from the venue.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0263223322781125e-19, \"text\": \"WSL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The movement began to gain widespread support, with anonline petition amassing over 100,000 signatures.\", \"from\": 385, \"to\": 488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked to comment, French Polynesian president Moetai Brotherson wassympathetic to the protesters, saying he \\\"had a reaction of solidarity.\\\"\", \"from\": 490, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 513, \"end\": 540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Polynesian president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 541, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moetai_Brotherson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Moetai Brotherson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moetai_Brotherson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moetai_Brotherson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He even went so far as to say that, had the decision been his to make, he would not have held the competition at Teahupo'o at all.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, he also stated that it would not be possible to reuse the WSL tower, due to logistical and safety concerns.\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0263223322781125e-19, \"text\": \"WSL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, in December, a construction bargedamaged the coral reef, prompting a suspension of work on the tower.\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 991, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In response, the International Surfing Association made a public statement, saying it would not support further construction.\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Surfing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Surfing Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Surfing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Surfing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite that, organizersreiterated that the tower would still be built.\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Changes were made to the construction plan and schedule, after which construction continued  After seeing the latest progress, Brotherson has changed his stance, asFrance 24reports.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am totally happy with how the work is going after the controversy over the judges' tower,\\\" he toldAFP.\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Polynesians have accepted the solution that was proposed.\\\"\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1479, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesian_culture\", \"score\": 0.5166819575266725, \"rank\": 0.8391622923775401, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesian_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesian_culture\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So far, around two thirds of the drilling has been done and they are going to start laying the foundation blocks,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have changed the format.\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are being very, very demanding with the builders,\\\" Brotherson went on.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All the work is being followed by our services and everything is going well.\\\"\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He concluded that no more coral had been broken since the December incident.\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the best.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1941, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We promise.\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 1953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Join our community of contributors.\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1990, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Inertia is part ofAllGear Digital'sportfolio of media brands.\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2057